    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-05-13T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-05-13T10:00:00-05:00" n="432"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d432">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">683.84A/5–1352: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 432<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Israel (<persName corresp="#p_DMB1"
                            type="from">Davis</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d432fn1">Repeated to Damascus and Jerusalem (for <persName
                            corresp="#p_RLG1">Riley</persName>).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tel Aviv</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-05-13T18:00:00+03:00"
                            >May 13, 1952—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1191. <gloss target="#t_UNTSO1">UNTSO</gloss> Chief of Staff advises that fol has
                    been reported to <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> under date of May 12. He
                    requests that Dept and Emb Damascus regard it as background and that content not
                    be discussed with Syrian reps. Content of message as fols: <pb facs="0969"
                        n="929" xml:id="pg_929"/>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“On subject of adjustment of demarcation line, the senior Syrian del to
                            the <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> asked the senior Israel del to
                            state the position of the former’s govt on this subject. The latter
                            replied in the presence of the <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss>
                            Chairman that the <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> was prepared to
                            undertake secret discussions at high level on Syria–Israel relations,
                            adding that in such discussions both parties submit any proposal and
                            raise any question they wished. The senior Syrian del inquired whether
                            the Israelis were proposing to discuss peace. Israel del replied in the
                            negative. Syrian del said he wld submit Israel’s proposal to his govt
                            forthwith but expressed as his personal opinion the belief his govt wld
                            not undertake discussions this nature without <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                                >UN</gloss> reps being present. <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss>
                            Chairman expects to see Syrian Chief of Staff May 14 or 15 and believes
                            high-level Israel-Syria talks may serve to reduce tension. Hence will
                            make every effort obtain affirmative answer from Syria.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DMB1">Davis</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
